article.description: — Cedric Coward's 25 points and 10 rebounds helped Eastern Washington defeat Portland Bible 103-34 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Coward scores 25 and grabs 10 rebounds as Eastern Washington takes down Portland Bible 103-34
article.linkText: Coward scores 25 and grabs 10 rebounds as Eastern Washington takes down Portland Bible 103-34
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- — Cedric Coward's 25 points and 10 rebounds helped Eastern Washington defeat Portland Bible 103-34 on Wednesday night. Coward added three steals for the Eagles (3-6). Dane Erikstrup added 17 points, 11 rebounds and five blocks. Ethan Price had 14 points and went 6 of 10 from the field. The Eagles shot 61% (42 of 69) from the field. Rashad Hickson led the Wildcats in scoring, finishing with nine points. Trevor Vermillion added eight points and seven rebounds for Portland Bible. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
